  "text": ", which forms a simple topic hierarchy. The idea here is that topics discussed in segments can be variants of topics of the whole document. [CITATION_1] have shown that this topic structure can significantly improve the modelling accuracy, which should contribute to more accurate segmentation. This generative process is different from PLDA. PLDA does not assume the document level topic distribution and each time generates the segment level topic distribution directly from a Dirichlet distribution.",
